【组合论证段（建议写入 Introduction）】：
  "We show that GUI grounding signals emerge in intermediate layers
  (L27-33 in our Qwen2.5-VL experiments) and collapse in the final layers,
  before the first output coordinate token is generated. This phenomenon is
  consistent with findings that ViTs discard spatial information in their
  final layers [Raghu et al., 2022], middle layers contain specialized
  representations for high-level contextual understanding [Gurnee et al.,
  2023], and intermediate representations can encode linearly decodable
  world-model features [Nanda et al., 2023]."

